{"key":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01|Ecc|3","bibleId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01","bookAbbr":"Ecc","chapter":3,"textRevision":"api-bible-csb-2024","parserRevision":"v10","verses":[{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:Ecc:3:1","bibleId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01","bookAbbr":"Ecc","bookOrder":20,"chapter":3,"verse":1,"text":"There is an occasion for everything,","textRevision":"api-bible-csb-2024"},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:Ecc:3:2","bibleId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01","bookAbbr":"Ecc","bookOrder":20,"chapter":3,"verse":2,"text":"a time to give birth and a time to die;","textRevision":"api-bible-csb-2024"},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:Ecc:3:3","bibleId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01","bookAbbr":"Ecc","bookOrder":20,"chapter":3,"verse":3,"text":"a time to kill and a time to heal;","textRevision":"api-bible-csb-2024"},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:Ecc:3:4","bibleId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01","bookAbbr":"Ecc","bookOrder":20,"chapter":3,"verse":4,"text":"a time to weep and a time to laugh;","textRevision":"api-bible-csb-2024"},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:Ecc:3:5","bibleId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01","bookAbbr":"Ecc","bookOrder":20,"chapter":3,"verse":5,"text":"a time to throw stones and a time to gather stones;","textRevision":"api-bible-csb-2024"},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:Ecc:3:6","bibleId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01","bookAbbr":"Ecc","bookOrder":20,"chapter":3,"verse":6,"text":"a time to search and a time to count as lost;","textRevision":"api-bible-csb-2024"},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:Ecc:3:7","bibleId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01","bookAbbr":"Ecc","bookOrder":20,"chapter":3,"verse":7,"text":"a time to tear and a time to sew;","textRevision":"api-bible-csb-2024"},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:Ecc:3:8","bibleId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01","bookAbbr":"Ecc","bookOrder":20,"chapter":3,"verse":8,"text":"a time to love and a time to hate;","textRevision":"api-bible-csb-2024"},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:Ecc:3:9","bibleId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01","bookAbbr":"Ecc","bookOrder":20,"chapter":3,"verse":9,"text":"What does the worker gain from his struggles?","textRevision":"api-bible-csb-2024"},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:Ecc:3:10","bibleId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01","bookAbbr":"Ecc","bookOrder":20,"chapter":3,"verse":10,"text":"I have seen the task that God has given the children of Adam to keep them occupied.","textRevision":"api-bible-csb-2024"},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:Ecc:3:11","bibleId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01","bookAbbr":"Ecc","bookOrder":20,"chapter":3,"verse":11,"text":"He has made everything appropriate in its time. He has also put eternity in their hearts, but no one can discover the work God has done from beginning to end.","textRevision":"api-bible-csb-2024"},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:Ecc:3:12","bibleId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01","bookAbbr":"Ecc","bookOrder":20,"chapter":3,"verse":12,"text":"I know that there is nothing better for them than to rejoice and enjoy the good life.","textRevision":"api-bible-csb-2024"},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:Ecc:3:13","bibleId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01","bookAbbr":"Ecc","bookOrder":20,"chapter":3,"verse":13,"text":"It is also the gift of God whenever anyone eats, drinks, and enjoys all his efforts.","textRevision":"api-bible-csb-2024"},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:Ecc:3:14","bibleId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01","bookAbbr":"Ecc","bookOrder":20,"chapter":3,"verse":14,"text":"I know that everything God does will last forever; there is no adding to it or taking from it. God works so that people will be in awe of him.","textRevision":"api-bible-csb-2024"},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:Ecc:3:15","bibleId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01","bookAbbr":"Ecc","bookOrder":20,"chapter":3,"verse":15,"text":"Whatever is, has already been, and whatever will be, already is. However, God seeks justice for the persecuted.","textRevision":"api-bible-csb-2024"},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:Ecc:3:16","bibleId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01","bookAbbr":"Ecc","bookOrder":20,"chapter":3,"verse":16,"text":"I also observed under the sun: there is wickedness at the place of judgment and there is wickedness at the place of righteousness.","textRevision":"api-bible-csb-2024"},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:Ecc:3:17","bibleId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01","bookAbbr":"Ecc","bookOrder":20,"chapter":3,"verse":17,"text":"I said to myself, “God will judge the righteous and the wicked, since there is a time for every activity and every work.”","textRevision":"api-bible-csb-2024"},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:Ecc:3:18","bibleId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01","bookAbbr":"Ecc","bookOrder":20,"chapter":3,"verse":18,"text":"I said to myself, “This happens so that God may test the children of Adam and they may see for themselves that they are like animals.”","textRevision":"api-bible-csb-2024"},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:Ecc:3:19","bibleId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01","bookAbbr":"Ecc","bookOrder":20,"chapter":3,"verse":19,"text":"For the fate of the children of Adam and the fate of animals is the same. As one dies, so dies the other; they all have the same breath. People have no advantage over animals since everything is futile.","textRevision":"api-bible-csb-2024"},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:Ecc:3:20","bibleId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01","bookAbbr":"Ecc","bookOrder":20,"chapter":3,"verse":20,"text":"All are going to the same place; all come from dust, and all return to dust.","textRevision":"api-bible-csb-2024"},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:Ecc:3:21","bibleId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01","bookAbbr":"Ecc","bookOrder":20,"chapter":3,"verse":21,"text":"Who knows if the spirits of the children of Adam go upward and the spirits of animals go downward to the earth?","textRevision":"api-bible-csb-2024"},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:Ecc:3:22","bibleId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01","bookAbbr":"Ecc","bookOrder":20,"chapter":3,"verse":22,"text":"I have seen that there is nothing better than for a person to enjoy his activities because that is his reward. For who can enable him to see what will happen after he dies?","textRevision":"api-bible-csb-2024"}],"layout":{"bibleId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01","bookAbbr":"Ecc","chapter":3,"paragraphStarts":[1,2,3,4,5,6,7,8,9,16],"headings":[{"beforeVerse":1,"text":"The Mystery of Time"},{"beforeVerse":16,"text":"The Mystery of Injustice and Death"}],"poetryBlocks":[{"beforeVerse":1,"level":1},{"beforeVerse":2,"level":1},{"beforeVerse":3,"level":1},{"beforeVerse":4,"level":1},{"beforeVerse":5,"level":1},{"beforeVerse":6,"level":1},{"beforeVerse":7,"level":1},{"beforeVerse":8,"level":1}],"studyByVerse":[{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:Ecc:3:1","parts":[{"kind":"text","text":"There is an occasion for everything,"}],"crossRefs":[],"footnotes":[]},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:Ecc:3:2","parts":[{"kind":"text","text":"a time to give birth and a time to die; "},{"kind":"crossref","label":"Jb 14:5","book":"Job","chapter":14,"verse":5,"letter":"a"},{"kind":"crossref","label":"Heb 9:27","book":"Heb","chapter":9,"verse":27,"letter":"b"}],"crossRefs":[{"label":"Jb 14:5","book":"Job","chapter":14,"verse":5},{"label":"Heb 9:27","book":"Heb","chapter":9,"verse":27}],"footnotes":[]},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:Ecc:3:3","parts":[{"kind":"text","text":"a time to kill and a time to heal;"}],"crossRefs":[],"footnotes":[]},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:Ecc:3:4","parts":[{"kind":"text","text":"a time to weep and a time to laugh; "},{"kind":"crossref","label":"Rm 12:15","book":"Rom","chapter":12,"verse":15,"letter":"a"}],"crossRefs":[{"label":"Rm 12:15","book":"Rom","chapter":12,"verse":15}],"footnotes":[]},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:Ecc:3:5","parts":[{"kind":"text","text":"a time to throw stones and a time to gather stones; "},{"kind":"crossref","label":"2Kg 3:19","book":"2Ki","chapter":3,"verse":19,"letter":"a"},{"kind":"crossref","label":"2Kg 3:25","book":"2Ki","chapter":3,"verse":25,"letter":"b"},{"kind":"crossref","label":"Is 5:2","book":"Isa","chapter":5,"verse":2,"letter":"c"}],"crossRefs":[{"label":"2Kg 3:19","book":"2Ki","chapter":3,"verse":19},{"label":"2Kg 3:25","book":"2Ki","chapter":3,"verse":25}